article.description: Lauren Prochaska scored 31 points and Bowling Green knocked off No. 23 Vanderbilt 79-68 on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Lauren Prochaska scores 31 as Bowling Green surprises Vandy
article.linkText: Bowling Green wins see-saw battle with Vandy
article.story:
BOWLING GREEN, Ohio -- Lauren Prochaska scored 31 points and Bowling Green knocked off No. 23 Vanderbilt 79-68 on Wednesday night.

Prochaska shot 8 of 16 from the field, including 5 of 9 from 3-point range, for the Falcons (7-1), who won their seventh straight game.

Prochaska also hit all 10 of her free throws to extend her streak to 53, breaking her own school record.

The game was tied seven times before Bowling Green used a 10-3 run to pull ahead 33-26 en route to a 44-32 halftime lead.

The Commodores (4-2) closed to 51-48 with 14:31 left, but Prochaska hit a 3-pointer and made three free throws to pad the cushion.

Jen Uhl added 15 points for Bowling Green.

Jasmine Lister, Jence Rhoads and Hannah Tuomi scored 14 points each for Vanderbilt, and Stephanie Holzer had 10 points in 10 minutes. Tuomi and Holzer spent much of the night in foul trouble.
